cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.DS 

This paper deals with a network communication problem involving real-time status updates and prioritized delivery to certain nodes. This falls under the scope of computer networks (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The analysis of the time-averaged age of information also involves concepts from control systems (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the use of shifted-exponential link delay distributions is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
